servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/creamy-mushroom-spaghetti-with-burrata-66a7cf66ff70d218deffb2e8
---

Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Place @burrata{4%ounce} in a #small bowl. Using two #forks, shred burrata into bite-size pieces. Drizzle with @olive oil{1%teaspoon} and season with @salt and @pepper; stir until combined and creamy. Set aside.

Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}.

== Lemony Toasted Panko ==

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}; season with @salt and @pepper. Cook, stirring frequently, until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Transfer to a second #small bowl; stir in as much lemon zest as you like. Wipe out pan.

== Mushroom Sauce and Pasta ==

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

While pasta cooks, heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in pan used for panko over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and scallion whites; season with @salt and @pepper. Cook, stirring, until browned and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. Add garlic; cook, stirring, ~{30%seconds} more.

Reduce heat to medium. Stir in @cream cheese{2%tablespoon}, 1/4 cup reserved pasta cooking water, and @butter{2%tablespoon} until thoroughly combined.

> For 4 servings, use 1/2 cup pasta cooking water and 4 TBSP butter.

Add drained spaghetti, scallion greens, and a big squeeze of lemon juice to pan with mushrooms; toss until pasta is evenly coated, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> If needed, stir in more reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time until everything is coated in a creamy sauce.

Taste and season with @salt and @pepper.

== To Serve ==

Divide pasta between shallow #bowls; sprinkle with panko and top with a dollop of seasoned burrata. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.